node.text: Cédric Grolet' s style is characterised by his creativity and his personality: his desserts, inspired by nature, have made him one of the best in the world, and set a gold standard in signature pastries. Grolet revives family recipes, giving them a personal touch, always with the same central character: fruits for Le Meurice and flowers for Opera. The collection will be on sale online and in selected stores. Find out the collection and the complete story at zarahome.com

node.text: Juana Pepa is argentinian but lives in Madrid with her husband and two children. Creative and multi-talented, Juana takes us on a journey, tells us stories and shows her love through food. Juana has a gift for transforming a daily ritual like eating into an experience, an emotion, a memory. Discover her tricks for making any event special in our latest editorial. Find out at zarahome.com

node.text: Discover our new bicycle capsule, in collaboration with @veloretti. Available in Spain and soon in more countries. Stay tuned! For Leia and Gary Sfez, and their three children, the arrival is spring gives way to idyllic Sundays in family. Starting with a drawn-out brunch in their sun-dappled Parisian apartment, they embrace the day by meandering around the city on bikes — carefree and curious. Find out the latest edit at #zarahome.com
